cs.DB, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.CY 

This paper proposes a method for performing differentially private aggregations on databases, which is a topic related to data management and privacy. Therefore, cs.DB (Database) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the privacy aspect of the proposed method, which suggests that it may belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper uses relational algebra and SQL engine, which are topics related to machine learning and data analysis, suggesting that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
